						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 44: 1113-14 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This epigraph records the gift of money in the coin in current use (<hi rend="italic">aṉṟāḍunaṟkāśu</hi>) by Kumāramuḻāṉ Vēḷāṉ Kākkunāyakaṉ of Dāmanallūr in Tirumuṉaippāḍi, for a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to god Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulavallinallūr in Pattāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. The gift was received by Gautaman Tiruvoṟṟikaṇḍaśiva[ṉ*].</p>						

						</summary>
